just_use WireAction.elm

# label: WORKHORSE (wire-action-v2)
# role: domain — action-shaped wire format for the LynRummy port

Action-shaped wire format. Each `WireAction` value names what
the player did (split, merge-stack, merge-hand, place-hand,
move-stack, complete-turn, undo); receiver derives post-state
by applying the action to prior state. No diff on the wire.

Wire is primitives-only. `TrickResult` (board diff) was
ripped on 2026-04-20 and `PlayTrick` (client convenience)
was ripped on 2026-04-21 when hints moved client-side (see
`project_hints_are_client_side.md`).

See `showell/claude_writings/actions_not_diffs.md` for rationale.

## Exposed surface

- `type WireAction` — 7 constructors: `Split`, `MergeStack`,
  `MergeHand`, `PlaceHand`, `MoveStack`, `CompleteTurn`,
  `Undo`. No `Draw`/`Discard` (LynRummy has no draw pile).
- `encode : WireAction -> Json.Encode.Value`
- `decoder : Json.Decode.Decoder WireAction`

## JSON shape (wire contract)

```
{"action":"split","stack_index":I,"card_index":I}
{"action":"merge_stack","source_stack":I,"target_stack":I,"side":S}
{"action":"merge_hand","hand_card":C,"target_stack":I,"side":S}
{"action":"place_hand","hand_card":C,"loc":L}
{"action":"move_stack","stack_index":I,"new_loc":L}
{"action":"complete_turn"}
{"action":"undo"}
```

Where `S = "left" | "right"`, `C = encoded Card`, `L = {top, left}`.

Stacks are referenced by **positional index** in the board
list (V1 choice). Hand cards are referenced by **content
identity** (Card, not HandCard — wire doesn't carry state).

## Tests

`tests/Game/WireActionTest.elm`:
- Round-trip (encode → decode → equal) for every constructor.
- Exact-JSON format tests for representative shapes to lock
  the wire contract against accidental drift.
- Decode-error tests (unknown tag, missing payload, bad side
  value, missing action tag).

## Pointers

- Consumers: `Main/Apply.elm` (outbound on player actions
  via `Main/Wire.elm`), server route
  `POST /gopher/lynrummy-elm/actions` (persists raw JSON
  into `lynrummy_elm_actions`), `Reducer.applyAction`
  (folds the log to state).
- Go counterpart: `games/lynrummy/wire_action.go` +
  `wire_action.claude`. Same shape. Cross-language
  conformance via `games/lynrummy/conformance/` scenarios
  + format-lock tests.
- Depends on: `Game.Rules.Card.encodeCard` / `cardDecoder`,
  `Game.CardStack.encodeBoardLocation` /
  `boardLocationDecoder`, `Game.BoardActions.Side`.
